                <p>The most important panel in your networking settings. Once a site has been set up with its data (the more the better) a <strong>symbiocard.csv</strong> file can be created by the site owner, and sent to people they wish to network with. <br />
                    <br />
                    You in turn upload the .csv file and the system uses the values it contains to populate local info in linking to them. Obviously they do the same for you. <br />
                    <br />
                    If you manually type in the address into the bar, your website will fetch the .csv file itself and (if it exists) will autopopulate info that way.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <h3 id="csv_file"><span class="description">Network  &mdash; </span>.csv and symbiocard Files Explained</h3>
                See also: <a href="http://www.symbiostock.com/how-does-symbiostock-promote-you/" title="How does symbiostock promote you?" target="_blank">"How Does Symbiostock Promote You?"</a>
                <p>Introducing the <strong>symbiocard!</strong> Its actually symbiocard.csv to be exact. The symbiocard can be likened to a "seed", such as a <a title="burdock" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arctium">burdock seed</a> or a <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Taraxacum">dandelion seed.</a><br />
                    <br />
                    The symbiocard actually "travels" the network based on user activity and promotes your site where relevant. Much like a burdock seed, it relies on human traffic to find its way around. Or much like a dendelion seed, it simply kites its way from one point to another. The little "symbiocard" an essential component in Symbiostock mutual promotion, since it viturally takes on a life course of its own in spreading your website's presence.</p>
                <p>Your site uses two very useful (and ancient!) web technologies to network. XML and .csv files. This allows your data to be machine-used in applications beyond mere web display. As Symbiostock grows, so will use of these simple data sharing languages.<br />
                    <br />
                    By clicking on the ",a," icon beside either your url or your network associate's, you can automatically fetch symbiocard.csv files for distribution. This is helpful, for instance, in setting up Symbiostock directories.<br />
                    <br />
                    You can update your symbiocard.csv file at any time by clicking the "Update public network info" checkbox at the bottom of your Symbiostock admin panels. It will then be generated as a "symbiocard.csv" file which will sit in your Wordpress install root, where in turn other Symbiostock sites will refer to update their information on you. This is also where the download link refers when you download your .csv file for sending to prospective network partners or hubs.</p>
                <span class="description"><strong>.csv</strong> - A comma-separated values or character-separated values (CSV) file is a simple text format for a database table. </span><br />
                <br />
                <span class="description"><strong>XML</strong> - Extensible Markup Language, a metalanguage that allows users to define their own customized markup languages.</span> </li>
            <li>
                <h3 id="author_settings"><span class="description">Network, Author Options (profile area)  &mdash; </span>Author Settings</h3>
